span>2<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> He has shaped the theoretical understanding of normal and superfluid helium liquids and strongly coupled superfluids.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Anthony_J._Leggett#cite_note-3\"><span>[<\/span>3<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> He set directions for research in the quantum physics of macroscopic <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Dissipative_system\" title=\"Dissipative system\">dissipative systems<\/a> and use of condensed systems to test the foundations of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Quantum_mechanics\" title=\"Quantum mechanics\">quantum mechanics<\/a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Anthony_J._Leggett#cite_note-4\"><span>[<\/span>4<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p>","name":"Anthony J. Leggett","place_of_birth":"Camberwell ,  London ,  England ,  UK","place_of_death":null,"text":"Anthony J. Leggett ,  born in United Kingdom , Physics, 2003","year":2003.0}